2) $f(x)=\tanh x-x+\int_{0}^{x} f^{\prime}(t) \tanh ^{2} t d t$
$\Rightarrow f^{\prime}(x)=\operatorname{sech}^{2} x-1+f^{\prime}(x) \tanh ^{2} x$
$\Rightarrow f^{\prime}(x)\left(1-\tanh ^{2} x\right)=\operatorname{sech}^{2} x-1$
$\Rightarrow f^{\prime}(x) \operatorname{sech}^{2} x=\operatorname{sech}^{2} x-1$
$\Rightarrow f^{\prime}(x)=1-\cosh ^{2} x=-\sinh ^{2} x$
따라서 $f(x)=\int-\sinh ^{2} x d x=-\int \frac{\cosh 2 x-1}{2} d x$
$$=-\frac{1}{2}\left(\frac{1}{2} \sinh 2 x-x\right)+C$$

이고, $f(0)=0$ 이므로 $C=0$ 이다.
즉, $f(\ln 2)=-\frac{1}{4} \sinh (2 \ln 2)+\frac{1}{2} \ln 2=-\frac{15}{32}+\frac{1}{2} \ln 2$
